description:
Integrate PostHog feature flags into the DataTools Pro application to control visibility of premium integration features. Snowflake, HubSpot, and Tableau features in the left toolbar should be disabled by default and enabled via PostHog feature flags.

Three feature flags were created in the PostHog dashboard. The PostHog PHP SDK is initialized during authentication, and user identity (email, name) is sent to PostHog via `PostHog::identify()`. This enables per-customer feature flag targeting in the PostHog dashboard.

Code implementation:
```php
PostHog::init(config('services.posthog.key'), [
    'host' => config('services.posthog.host'),
]);
PostHog::identify($userDB->id, [
    'email' => $userDB->email,
    'name'  => trim($userDB->firstname . ' ' . $userDB->lastname),
]);
```
